        5/8/2017
    

Fantastic Crew, terrible back office support and terrible infrastructure. Most of the HSBC employees phone agents and tellers have a polite demeanour & best intentions. On the contrary the banking system and norms they use are really painstaking. My time to open an account for a promotion I received was 1 hour and 30 mins, that included a waiting for ~15 mins, account details gathering for ~20 mins, waiting for ~30 mins and then finally ~25 mins with the teller. HSBC corporate run promotions without staffing the local branch with the right infrastructure. In my case, they couldn't accept the check because they let me walk in at 2:30p and by the time they could operate my account they were over 4:00p.Now let's get to the promotion itself, no one from the call center or the administration team could tell you whether you are on track or not to receive your bonus, in fact the call center team has no clue what promotion you signed up on. They will ask you to reach via Bankmail(their secure messaging platform) and the mail team will redirect you to the call center. Its cyclic! Now if you were reading between the lines, my frustration is not the promotion. For a global bank of this footprint, their card systems, online account management, 4 websites before you can sign in, 40 mins of call wait time and the whole experience is so terrible. So in short, not only avoid this branch, (great staff) AVOID THE BANK like plague for domestic US banking at the least.




