        10/31/2016
    

So my reason visiting the bank was to open a new checking account and take advantage of their promotional sign up. First off when entering the bank I was confused and felt lost. The entrance to the bank is not the traditional Chase or BofA. You walk pass the advisers offices before reaching the teller at the end of the hallway. Layout of the bank I would give 1 star because it didn't feel welcoming at all. I met the teller first, Christine a traditional Chinese lady. If you understand the Chinese culture then you know what I mean. She handed me some documents to fill out but didn't give me a pen. Luckily I had my own. Towards the end of my trip, she opened up more and I was able to understand the banking process more there. I give her 3.5 stars.The person who assisted me in opening up my account was Jeff Liao. I was pretty honest with my feelings with the bank and told him I felt foreign in entering the banking facility. He is a very nice person and took the time to explain to me the different options they have. He was pretty patient and was able to answer all the questions I have and even walked me through th online sign on process. I would give him 5 stars, strongly recommend him if you need services at the bank. There was another lady, her office was second to the right of the teller. She looked like the Dragon lady at the office. Not friendly or helpful when she saw me and pretty much ignored me. I would give her 0 stars...I'm just so very glad Jeff made my experience at HSBC bank so much better. Also, I wouldn't recommend coming here in a rush, their computer system is pretty slow.




