        5/24/2012
    

Let me first sum up that this is NOT your bank... "You are NOT a customer, you're an asset".They seem nice and are very willing to help you setup an account, but that's because you've given them control of your money.  Once they have your money, they act like they are doing you a service by controlling it.They can decide NOT to give you your money.  Yes you heard right, they refused a cash with drawl from the teller.  Not because of insufficient funds or due to not having the proper ID and account information.   They suggest that they don't always have sufficient funds to allow for cash with drawls sums that are perfectly ok at other banks (BofA for example).   If you with drawl funds regularly this is NOT the bank for you.The place seems more like an old world investment bank.  Between the teller in the back, the sense of questioning as to why you would make a with drawl, the rude Indian manager... If you ask for your money, expect resistance and even a fight.  With all the headache they caused, i can't say enough of how frustrating it is to work with this bank.   Yes most banks suck for one reason or another, but in the end all the other banks never refused me access to my money.




