            Log In
        











 









2





567 University AvePalo Alto, CA 94301


        (650) 321-8005
    






This is my first yelp review, which I decided to write because the manager at this HSBC branch went WAY WAY above and beyond helping me with a problem with an overseas HSBC account. She spent over an hour with me placing calls, downloading forms, helping me get them completed and sent off, and she was pleasant and patient through the entire process. I have no complaints about my current bank, but this experience raises the bar for what I consider to be excellent customer service. If I lived closer to Palo Alto, I would be very happy to do my banking here.







If the system let me do zero star, I will.  This is the most ridiculous operation,  a sorry excuse for a bank.  Went in for my safe deposit box during bank hour after driving across town and lucky enough to find a parking place (don't get me started on the parking but I guess that is not quite their fault).  They have the nerve to tell me that they are short staffed and everyone else is in a meeting so they cannot access the safe deposit box.  I can come back in 3-4 hours or make an appointment.

Why have bank hours if they can selectively decide certain service will not be available?  Maybe they should take a class in managing workload and resource balancing.  They are here to service the customers, not arbitrarily decide what they would not do for the day.  So frustrated with HSBC.







            HSBC
        






