If the system let me do zero star, I will.  This is the most ridiculous operation,  a sorry excuse for a bank.  Went in for my safe deposit box during bank hour after driving across town and lucky enough to find a parking place (don't get me started on the parking but I guess that is not quite their fault).  They have the nerve to tell me that they are short staffed and everyone else is in a meeting so they cannot access the safe deposit box.  I can come back in 3-4 hours or make an appointment.Why have bank hours if they can selectively decide certain service will not be available?  Maybe they should take a class in managing workload and resource balancing.  They are here to service the customers, not arbitrarily decide what they would not do for the day.  So frustrated with HSBC.




